The National Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Uche Secondus on Wednesday led hundreds of PDP members, including the newly elected governors of Adamawa and Imo states, to the Government House, Port Harcourt to congratulate Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers State on his re-election.
Secondus during the visit to commended his fellow Rivers sons and daughters of Rivers State for standing firm even in the face of the violence, molestation and killings they suffered while defending their votes and democracy. He assured of better years ahead.







			
